            <title>[BOOKKEEPER-61] BufferedChannel read endless when the remaining bytes of file is less than the capacity of read buffer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-61</link>
                <project id="12311293" key="BOOKKEEPER">Bookkeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If last record in entry log file is truncated (length of data is short than expected length), bookie went into infinite loop on reading this record.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A truncated record can be caused in following cases:&lt;br/&gt;
1) bookie server is killed during bookie restart to relay logs.&lt;br/&gt;
2) bookie server is killed when bookie does adding entry operation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
